&nbsp; The Kenya National Chamber of Commerce and Industry (KNCCI) National Chairman Kiprono Kittony has been appointed Vice Chairman of the World Chamber Federation (WCF). The appointment that took effect earlier this month, will see him represent the African continent in the lobby until December next year. Prior to his appointment, Mr Kittony (abovee) served as a council member of WCF. The development is expected to boost Kenya&rsquo;s quest to host the 2021 World Chambers Congress. ALSO READ: Danger lurks in roads, parks turned into trading stalls